messages.message: @Dominic Fannjiang do you need to use a commercial account? Can you create a new, separate personal account to continue working?
to my understanding, I need a commercial account to test a commercial feature locally, unless there is another way I can do it without creating my own

OK, yes. First add:
```    "metronome_api_key": "66b1e9fa781500eea2f4a2513af108e3569c724d52b09b89ba3c75b8ee9db269",```
To env-local.json and recompile/restart api-server, webapp, celery-app-tasks.

In the meantime, I'll make sure the org that your user belongs to is set up correctly. If you know the orgname off the top of your head, or if you can create a new org instead (_after_ following the instructions above), that will help.
Just created a new org with my services compiled with the metronome api key. org id is `domfj-local-organization`
OK, in theory you're good to go, depending on when you last rebased :slightly_smiling_face:
But lmk if not.
